Gregg M. Sherrill


Gregg Sherrill assumed the role of executive chairman of Tenneco’s Board of Directors in May 2017, after serving for 10 years as chairman and CEO. Tenneco is an $8.6 billion global manufacturer of clean air and ride performance components and systems. With approximately 31,000 employees across 23 countries, the company serves all major vehicle manufacturers and replacement market customers worldwide. During Gregg’s tenure as CEO, Tenneco established a strong track record of revenue growth, higher earnings and improved profitability.
Prior to joining Tenneco in January 2007, Gregg was with Johnson Controls, Inc., where he last served as president of the Power Solutions Group, the company’s global automotive battery business. Previously, he held leadership roles in JCI’s Automotive Systems Group and North America Operations. Gregg began his 40-year career in the automotive industry with Ford Motor Company, where he served in a broad range of engineering and manufacturing positions during a 22-year tenure.
Gregg serves on the Board of Directors for Snap-on Incorporated and on the Executive Committee of the National Association of Manufacturers, where he is also past chairman of the board. In addition, he is a member of the National Governing Council of The Wilderness Society.
In October 2015, Gregg received the Leadership in the Nation’s Interest Award from The Conference Board’s Committee for Economic Development, presented annually to business leaders who lead their companies with the utmost integrity and purpose and who champion public policies for the common good.
Gregg earned an MBA degree in Management from the Kelley School in 1991. He also holds a BS degree in mechanical engineering from Texas A&M University.
Gregg resides with his wife Sabine and their son Tyler in Lake Forest, Illinois, and they also enjoy their home and ranch in Wyoming. He has four adult daughters and 11 grandchildren.










